1
00:01:08,360 --> 00:01:09,760
I'm her ex-husband.

2
00:01:09,840 --> 00:01:12,040
Are you crazy?
My boss has never been married.

3
00:01:12,120 --> 00:01:13,800
Is IngIng your boss?

4
00:01:13,880 --> 00:01:15,760
I think it's possible
they're still together

5
00:01:15,840 --> 00:01:17,440
<i>and trying to trick you.</i>

6
00:01:17,520 --> 00:01:20,160
<i>That's impossible.</i>
<i>Ing would never lie to me.</i>

7
00:01:21,840 --> 00:01:24,640
You're so quick to pay me, huh?
Your new girlfriend must be rich.

8
00:01:24,720 --> 00:01:26,000
Ms. Lin has nothing to do with this.

9
00:01:26,520 --> 00:01:27,960
I'll get the money myself.

10
00:01:29,120 --> 00:01:30,400
How much do you want?

11
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:32,040
<i>It's him. I'm certain.</i>

12
00:01:32,120 --> 00:01:35,280
<i>I remember IngIng's ex-husband clearly.</i>

13
00:01:41,080 --> 00:01:43,960
RECHARGE STATION

14
00:01:57,600 --> 00:01:59,720
Here's the brochure
for the new tutoring school,

15
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:01,280
in case you're interested.

16
00:02:01,360 --> 00:02:02,880
Please register here.

17
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:04,160
- Register here.
- Can I have one?

18
00:02:04,240 --> 00:02:05,760
- Hello.
- Thank you.

19
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:08,800
This tutoring school will be opening here,
replacing Play Park.

20
00:02:08,880 --> 00:02:10,080
When will it open?

21
00:02:10,160 --> 00:02:12,040
At the end of this month
or early next month.

22
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:13,680
If you're interested,
please feel free to register.

23
00:02:13,760 --> 00:02:14,960
- Okay.
- Yes.

24
00:02:15,040 --> 00:02:16,640
- Thank you.
- Please register here.

25
00:02:16,720 --> 00:02:18,640
- Here's the brochure. Hello.
- Yes.

26
00:02:18,720 --> 00:02:22,000
- Thank you.
- Please register here.

27
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:23,640
- All done.
- Yes.

28
00:02:23,720 --> 00:02:26,480
- Can I scan to pay?
- Of course.

29
00:02:26,560 --> 00:02:28,360
- Go ahead.
- Okay, let me scan it.

30
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:29,800
- Yes.
- Thank you.

31
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:31,360
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

32
00:02:31,440 --> 00:02:33,880
- Can I scan too?
- Of course.

33
00:02:34,760 --> 00:02:36,280
Thank you.

34
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:52,160
Why didn't you answer my call, Ms. Lin?

35
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:55,360
I didn't hear it.
Maybe my phone was on silent.

36
00:02:56,480 --> 00:02:58,000
Ah.

37
00:02:59,040 --> 00:03:01,960
This is the list of students
who have registered.

38
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:06,240
As for the money,
I've transferred it all to the company.

39
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:08,920
And my commission

40
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:11,480
is as we agreed.

41
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:15,720
Would you like to wait for the monthly
total, or should I transfer it now?

42
00:03:17,160 --> 00:03:18,600
You can transfer it now.

43
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:27,080
THAI QR PAYMENT

44
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:45,600
Thank you.

45
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:49,440
<i>I think it's possible</i>
<i>they're still together</i>

46
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:50,800
<i>and trying to trick you.</i>

47
00:03:50,880 --> 00:03:53,720
That's impossible.
Ing would never lie to me.

48
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:56,840
You never know, Ms. Lin.
Appearances can be misleading.

49
00:03:57,520 --> 00:03:59,960
<i>And the two of you</i>
<i>haven't known each other</i>

50
00:04:00,040 --> 00:04:01,400
<i>that long, right?</i>

51
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:06,240
<i>It's him. I'm certain.</i>
<i>I remember IngIng's ex-husband clearly.</i>

52
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:10,760
<i>They must be working together.</i>
<i>You're being scammed, Ms. Lin.</i>

53
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:17,279
<i>I'm trying to forget</i>
<i>everything that happened.</i>

54
00:04:19,399 --> 00:04:22,760
<i>I'm just telling myself</i>
<i>it was all a misunderstanding.</i>

55
00:04:33,760 --> 00:04:35,000
I'm heading home now.

56
00:04:35,520 --> 00:04:37,040
Drive safely.

57
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:39,120
Mm. See you later.

58
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:40,920
Mm.

59
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:43,080
Don't forget to miss me.

60
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:52,800
Bye-bye.

61
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:07,760
<i>I won't push you for the truth</i>

62
00:05:08,520 --> 00:05:11,640
<i>because I'm afraid</i>
<i>I'll hear something I don't want to hear.</i>

63
00:05:45,160 --> 00:05:46,520
How much is left?

64
00:05:48,880 --> 00:05:50,920
We still have time to find the rest.

65
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:52,600
Want me to transfer it?

66
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:55,600
No.

67
00:05:56,320 --> 00:06:00,160
Save your money.
This is my problem. I can handle it.

68
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:02,440
Then…

69
00:06:04,640 --> 00:06:05,920
should we borrow from Ms. Lin?

70
00:06:08,320 --> 00:06:10,120
Drop that idea.

71
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:13,640
I don't like it.

72
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:15,080
Why not?

73
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:18,400
We're just borrowing it.
We'll pay her back soon.

74
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:22,920
She won't let us repay her.

75
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:26,960
‪We need to believe
‪we can stand on our own.

76
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:30,920
I don't want this
to turn into a debt of gratitude.

77
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:36,680
She already feels bad enough for me.

78
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:42,280
Okay, okay.

79
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:45,960
Then I'll find a full-time job.

80
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:50,080
It's my turn to support our family.

81
00:06:55,320 --> 00:06:57,400
That's great, bro.

82
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:01,000
Let's see… how much is left?

83
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,920
- Let me total it up again.
- Mm.

84
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:07,880
SEPTEMBER'S EXPENSES

85
00:07:07,960 --> 00:07:11,000
LILIN

86
00:07:15,440 --> 00:07:16,720
Yes?

87
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:19,680
I'm coming to pick you up.
Let's have lunch.

88
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:23,680
I'm already out taking care of something.

89
00:07:23,760 --> 00:07:25,680
Maybe another time?

90
00:07:25,760 --> 00:07:27,560
Then we'll talk later.

91
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:29,440
Okay.

92
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:33,480
I'll be right back.

93
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:09,800
LILIN FAMILYNEST SENT A PHOTO

94
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:26,720
MS. LILIN

95
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,320
Hello, Ms. Lin.

96
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:32,080
Is that IngIng's ex-husband
in the photos I sent you?

97
00:09:32,160 --> 00:09:34,760
Yes, it's definitely him.

98
00:09:36,680 --> 00:09:38,360
How did you find him, Ms. Lin?

99
00:09:39,760 --> 00:09:41,520
I have to go. I'll tell you later.

100
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:56,440
Look, look.

101
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:14,680
Ms. Lin?

102
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:18,680
Ing is out on business.

103
00:10:19,280 --> 00:10:20,960
You should've called first.

104
00:10:22,040 --> 00:10:23,600
I thought I'd surprise her.

105
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:26,400
What's she out doing?

106
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:30,480
I have no idea. I didn't ask.

107
00:10:31,560 --> 00:10:34,520
‪Ing has been taking on jobs lately.

108
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:38,920
Yeah. IngIng seems so busy with work
that she hasn't had time to see me.

109
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:42,560
Do you have an urgent need for money?

110
00:10:45,760 --> 00:10:49,800
If you're having problems, you can
always talk to me, Ith. Don't be shy.

111
00:10:53,160 --> 00:10:55,160
Are you keeping something from me?

112
00:10:58,600 --> 00:10:59,440
No.

113
00:11:00,960 --> 00:11:02,080
Actually…

114
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:05,320
Ing wanted to…

115
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:08,280
save money for Donut

116
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:11,640
for when he starts school.

117
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:16,160
Yeah.

118
00:11:18,160 --> 00:11:19,680
Let's go play. Okay?

119
00:11:19,760 --> 00:11:22,840
Come on. Let's go.

120
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:25,440
Let's go play. Here.

121
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:52,560
Please wait until the end of the month.
Don't change your mind yet.

122
00:11:53,160 --> 00:11:54,400
Call me when you're ready.

123
00:11:54,920 --> 00:11:55,960
Yes, sir.

124
00:11:57,400 --> 00:11:58,440
Goodbye.

125
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:06,160
Satisfied now?
My car will definitely sell.

126
00:12:07,320 --> 00:12:08,360
Okay.

127
00:12:12,760 --> 00:12:14,000
Wait.

128
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:16,160
Can you drop me off at the same place?

129
00:12:16,920 --> 00:12:18,040
There are plenty of taxis here.

130
00:12:18,560 --> 00:12:19,640
What?

131
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:44,120
Here you go, ma'am.

132
00:12:52,560 --> 00:12:54,120
Ms. Lin, you have to stay firm.

133
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:57,920
The evidence couldn't be clearer.
They're tricking you.

134
00:13:01,560 --> 00:13:04,880
Let me collect myself first,
then I'll talk to Ing.

135
00:13:06,520 --> 00:13:09,920
She won't admit it.
She probably already has an excuse ready.

136
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:12,480
And you'll probably believe her again,
like you always do.

137
00:13:13,240 --> 00:13:15,240
Give me some time.

138
00:13:16,960 --> 00:13:20,200
It's best to move on quickly. Right now,

139
00:13:20,280 --> 00:13:22,480
a big responsibility is waiting for you.

140
00:13:26,880 --> 00:13:30,840
I learned that
your aunt is about to take over a factory.

141
00:13:30,920 --> 00:13:32,800
There's no time to waste.

142
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:47,480
Hello, Tutor's dad.

143
00:13:47,560 --> 00:13:48,520
Right here, please.

144
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:50,080
RECHARGE STATION

145
00:13:50,160 --> 00:13:51,640
Hello.

146
00:13:51,720 --> 00:13:53,440
Hello.

147
00:13:54,040 --> 00:13:56,320
- Oh, you're wearing sunglasses too.
- Thank you.

148
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:57,960
Thank you.

149
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:04,240
Hello. Please register here. Yes.

150
00:14:09,560 --> 00:14:12,000
Can a 60-year-old uncle sign up for this?

151
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:14,240
Mr. Pao!

152
00:14:21,760 --> 00:14:22,880
- Mr. Pao.
- Hm?

153
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:26,280
Well, well.

154
00:14:26,360 --> 00:14:29,080
Thought you weren't coming
to see us anymore.

155
00:14:29,680 --> 00:14:31,240
I had to come.

156
00:14:32,840 --> 00:14:36,120
But something's been bothering me.

157
00:14:36,880 --> 00:14:38,120
What is it?

158
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:42,400
Ms. Lin's father called me.

159
00:14:43,920 --> 00:14:46,080
He was worried

160
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:49,280
and asked me to find a way

161
00:14:49,360 --> 00:14:51,040
to close Play Park as soon as possible.

162
00:14:52,440 --> 00:14:53,560
And now

163
00:14:54,720 --> 00:14:58,680
there's trouble at my house,
and I need his help.

164
00:14:59,560 --> 00:15:03,280
But I don't have the courage to face him.

165
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:06,560
I'm at my wits' end.

166
00:15:07,160 --> 00:15:10,760
Can you help me?

167
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:19,080
We decided to postpone
Play Park's closure indefinitely.

168
00:15:22,160 --> 00:15:23,000
Manager!

169
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:29,760
Ms. Lin, please be honest.

170
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:33,440
Did you put off
Play Park's closing date indefinitely

171
00:15:34,840 --> 00:15:36,160
because of me?

172
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:38,520
I feel really bad

173
00:15:41,480 --> 00:15:43,640
for causing trouble
between you and your father.

174
00:15:44,320 --> 00:15:46,320
Don't blame yourself.

175
00:15:47,640 --> 00:15:50,160
I didn't do it to please you.

176
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:54,760
I really agree with your idea.

177
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:05,480
I'll resign, Mr. Pao.

178
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:10,680
It's probably for the best.

179
00:16:29,920 --> 00:16:33,760
Ms. Lin is attending a company seminar
in Pattaya for three days and two nights.

180
00:16:39,240 --> 00:16:40,760
Excuse me, sir.

181
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:47,600
Ms. IngIng, the Play Park manager,
is here to see you.

182
00:16:47,680 --> 00:16:49,160
Shall I let her in?

183
00:16:54,400 --> 00:16:55,440
Let her in.

184
00:17:22,800 --> 00:17:25,119
Okay, what does Fifi look like?

185
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:27,440
She has round eyes.

186
00:17:27,520 --> 00:17:28,720
Okay, round eyes.

187
00:18:08,760 --> 00:18:13,000
<i>Are you free this afternoon? Can we meet?</i>

188
00:18:14,360 --> 00:18:16,160
<i>If you're not, that's okay.</i>

189
00:18:57,600 --> 00:18:58,480
Have you been waiting long?

190
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:00,440
I just got here too.

191
00:19:09,840 --> 00:19:11,560
Is there something
you wanted to talk about?

192
00:19:20,960 --> 00:19:24,880
Do you still want to attend the seminar
in Pattaya that I invited you to?

193
00:19:24,960 --> 00:19:26,800
Oh.

194
00:19:27,840 --> 00:19:29,320
I thought it was something else.

195
00:19:32,480 --> 00:19:33,440
I'll go.

196
00:19:34,640 --> 00:19:36,040
Let's go, let's go.

197
00:20:20,760 --> 00:20:22,400
How was that even a breakup, Ms. Lin?

198
00:20:22,480 --> 00:20:25,800
She lied to you so much,
and you're still going on a trip with her?

199
00:20:26,480 --> 00:20:29,800
Before it ends badly,
can't we at least have some good memories?

200
00:20:31,560 --> 00:20:33,920
I really don't understand you.

201
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:39,800
Since I started dating Ing,
it's felt like a dream, Jane.

202
00:20:39,880 --> 00:20:41,760
I've been really happy.

203
00:20:46,720 --> 00:20:49,520
I don't know if I'll ever meet
someone like her again.

204
00:20:52,360 --> 00:20:53,560
You will.

205
00:20:53,640 --> 00:20:55,680
My Ms. Lin is lucky.

206
00:20:55,760 --> 00:20:57,840
You'll never meet a liar like that again.

207
00:20:58,440 --> 00:21:00,440
Please don't give in, Ms. Lin.

208
00:21:00,520 --> 00:21:03,800
You have to end this
and throw it into the sea.

209
00:21:04,720 --> 00:21:07,000
But I really love Ing.

210
00:21:08,640 --> 00:21:09,680
Love?

211
00:21:12,400 --> 00:21:16,160
If that's the case, you might as well
throw yourself into the sea too.

212
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:19,200
‪Please excuse me.

213
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:21,120
Oh?

214
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:23,800
- Where are you going, Jane?
- To the beach.

215
00:21:23,880 --> 00:21:26,160
Come back. I still have more to say.

216
00:21:41,360 --> 00:21:43,080
Woohoo!

217
00:21:43,160 --> 00:21:45,760
Woohoo!

218
00:21:46,280 --> 00:21:48,320
- Hey, the diapers are here.
- Mm.

219
00:21:48,400 --> 00:21:49,720
The washed cloth diapers are here.

220
00:21:50,680 --> 00:21:52,200
How long will you be gone?

221
00:21:52,720 --> 00:21:54,360
- Three days and two nights.
- Yeah.

222
00:21:55,200 --> 00:21:57,400
Donut's supplies will last a month.

223
00:21:59,840 --> 00:22:02,720
Just go.
Don't keep your girlfriend waiting.

224
00:22:04,080 --> 00:22:09,520
You talk too much. Mama will be back soon.
Stay with Uncle Ith, okay?

225
00:22:09,600 --> 00:22:11,680
Be a good boy.

226
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:14,400
Come here.

227
00:22:14,480 --> 00:22:16,080
You're getting heavier every day.

228
00:22:16,160 --> 00:22:17,160
Ugh.

229
00:22:18,120 --> 00:22:21,480
Have fun, sis.
And don't just stay in your room.

230
00:22:22,760 --> 00:22:23,920
I know.

231
00:22:25,920 --> 00:22:28,160
If anything comes up, call me anytime.

232
00:22:29,320 --> 00:22:31,640
Pattaya's just a phone call away, right?

233
00:22:31,720 --> 00:22:33,720
I'll be back before you know it.

234
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:35,800
- Go.
- Yeah.

235
00:22:40,440 --> 00:22:42,120
- Bye-bye. Bye-bye.
- I'm heading out.

236
00:22:42,200 --> 00:22:43,960
- Bye-bye!
- Bye-bye.

237
00:22:44,040 --> 00:22:46,920
- Bye-bye.
- Bye-bye. Bye-bye.

238
00:22:47,520 --> 00:22:48,400
Bye-bye?

239
00:22:50,960 --> 00:22:52,680
Come on. Let's go see Mama off.

240
00:22:59,080 --> 00:23:00,240
- Donut!
- Come on, bye-bye.

241
00:23:00,320 --> 00:23:03,200
- Bye-bye!
- Bye-bye. Wave bye-bye.

242
00:23:03,280 --> 00:23:04,880
I'm going now.

243
00:23:08,520 --> 00:23:10,160
- I'm leaving now, Ith.
- Yeah.

244
00:23:10,240 --> 00:23:12,560
- Bye-bye. Let's go.
- Let's go.

245
00:23:12,640 --> 00:23:14,680
Ith, take good care of him for me.

246
00:23:15,240 --> 00:23:18,120
Look, Mama's leaving. Look at her. See?

247
00:23:19,360 --> 00:23:25,480
She's heading off now. Bye-bye.
Whoa, don't follow her.

248
00:23:26,400 --> 00:23:28,800
Come on. It's just you and me now.

249
00:23:29,840 --> 00:23:32,120
You're confused? Let's go inside.

250
00:23:38,040 --> 00:23:42,880
<i>Mom said you're lovely</i>
<i>Dad said you're wonderful</i>

251
00:23:42,960 --> 00:23:47,280
<i>My siblings also said</i>
<i>That you're the one for me</i>

252
00:23:47,360 --> 00:23:49,840
<i>You take care of me tirelessly</i>

253
00:23:49,920 --> 00:23:52,920
<i>It'd be really hard not to love you</i>

254
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:56,560
<i>Because everything about you</i>
<i>Ticks my boxes, ticks my boxes</i>

255
00:23:56,640 --> 00:23:58,640
<i>You tick all my boxes</i>

256
00:25:02,240 --> 00:25:04,040
I don't see the beach anywhere.

257
00:25:05,760 --> 00:25:09,840
You said we were going to the beach.
Why are we at the Renaissance?

258
00:25:13,360 --> 00:25:14,240
Oh.

259
00:25:14,840 --> 00:25:16,920
And this is a double bed?

260
00:25:17,520 --> 00:25:18,640
Don't they have twin rooms?

261
00:25:19,680 --> 00:25:20,680
They're fully booked.

262
00:25:22,560 --> 00:25:23,720
That's such a classic excuse.

263
00:25:24,640 --> 00:25:25,760
Really.

264
00:25:33,680 --> 00:25:35,640
Did you bring a swimsuit?

265
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:39,160
Let's go swimming.

266
00:25:40,640 --> 00:25:42,920
We can go tomorrow.
We still have two more nights.

267
00:25:43,600 --> 00:25:47,280
You might not feel like swimming tomorrow.
Let's go today.

268
00:25:49,880 --> 00:25:51,080
That's true.

269
00:25:51,160 --> 00:25:52,600
Let's get changed.

270
00:25:57,840 --> 00:26:00,920
Hurry up, let's go.

271
00:30:21,360 --> 00:30:25,840
<i>I shouldn't keep secrets</i>
<i>from Ms. Lin, right?</i>

272
00:30:27,280 --> 00:30:30,120
<i>Should I tell her everything now?</i>

273
00:30:33,800 --> 00:30:36,040
<i>Should I just break up with her?</i>

274
00:30:36,120 --> 00:30:39,160
<i>Or should we slowly drift</i>
<i>into just being friends?</i>

275
00:30:40,080 --> 00:30:41,360
<i>What should I do?</i>

276
00:30:57,960 --> 00:30:59,520
Are you okay, Ms. Lin?

277
00:31:01,920 --> 00:31:04,760
You've seemed distracted since we arrived.

278
00:31:06,240 --> 00:31:09,880
Oh, I just have some work on my mind.

279
00:31:13,040 --> 00:31:14,320
Mm.

280
00:31:14,400 --> 00:31:16,960
It's okay
if you don't think about other women.

281
00:31:24,840 --> 00:31:27,960
Then I'm going to bed.

282
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:32,480
You can go ahead and sleep.
I'm not tired yet.

283
00:31:36,160 --> 00:31:37,640
Don't make me wait too long.

284
00:33:09,600 --> 00:33:12,720
Thank you.
Let's travel together again sometime.

285
00:33:17,600 --> 00:33:19,400
Do you want to go inside and rest?

286
00:33:20,240 --> 00:33:23,520
It's okay. I'll stop by Play Park
for a bit and then head home.

287
00:33:25,240 --> 00:33:27,480
Oh. Okay.

288
00:33:33,320 --> 00:33:34,800
Did you forget something?

289
00:34:01,640 --> 00:34:03,240
ENGINE START / STOP

290
00:34:24,480 --> 00:34:25,760
Oh?

291
00:34:32,480 --> 00:34:34,239
Are you heading to the seminar now?

292
00:34:34,840 --> 00:34:35,760
Yes.

293
00:34:40,960 --> 00:34:42,760
Do you need your luggage too?

294
00:34:43,840 --> 00:34:46,440
Oh, I'll be staying in a different room.

295
00:34:47,600 --> 00:34:50,280
Huh? Why?

296
00:34:50,920 --> 00:34:52,880
We have a small team meeting tonight,

297
00:34:53,400 --> 00:34:55,360
and I don't want to disturb you.

298
00:34:57,720 --> 00:34:58,600
Okay.

299
00:35:25,040 --> 00:35:29,240
Donut? Donut? Mama's home.

300
00:35:36,280 --> 00:35:37,400
Where is he?

301
00:35:44,360 --> 00:35:45,920
Is he upstairs?

302
00:36:04,560 --> 00:36:06,520
Ith, where's Donut?

303
00:36:08,360 --> 00:36:09,280
He's downstairs.

304
00:36:10,160 --> 00:36:11,680
Downstairs? He's not there.

305
00:36:11,760 --> 00:36:16,000
How could he not be there? I put him
to sleep, then I came up to take a shower.

306
00:36:19,840 --> 00:36:21,880
Where is he? He's not there.

307
00:37:17,120 --> 00:37:20,000
DEAR CUSTOMERS
PLAY PARK IS TEMPORARILY CLOSED

308
00:37:27,800 --> 00:37:29,120
Did you find him, sis?

309
00:37:29,840 --> 00:37:30,760
Did you find him?

310
00:37:31,320 --> 00:37:32,840
How could a baby
just disappear like that, Ith?

311
00:37:34,400 --> 00:37:36,440
I haven't gone anywhere since you left.

312
00:37:41,360 --> 00:37:44,280
When I came in, the gate was open.

313
00:37:47,120 --> 00:37:48,000
Or…

314
00:37:49,880 --> 00:37:51,400
could Donut have been kidnapped?

315
00:37:54,400 --> 00:37:55,960
Where's the stroller?

316
00:37:59,840 --> 00:38:02,160
Guy. It's Guy.

317
00:38:27,520 --> 00:38:29,320
No… Donut…

318
00:38:29,920 --> 00:38:30,960
Did he pick up?

319
00:38:35,320 --> 00:38:37,480
Who else could it be?

320
00:38:53,360 --> 00:38:54,760
Donut?

321
00:39:08,920 --> 00:39:10,480
He's with him.

322
00:39:11,000 --> 00:39:12,280
He's with him, Ith.

323
00:39:12,360 --> 00:39:13,520
It's okay.

324
00:39:14,760 --> 00:39:17,360
We'll find him. We'll find him soon.

325
00:39:39,720 --> 00:39:42,880
- Hello, Ms. Lin.
- Hello, Ms. Lin.

326
00:39:42,960 --> 00:39:45,240
Why is Play Park closed?
What repairs are being done?

327
00:39:46,680 --> 00:39:48,680
Didn't you order it to close?

328
00:39:49,360 --> 00:39:50,320
No.

329
00:39:50,960 --> 00:39:53,800
But Family Nest ordered the closure.

330
00:39:53,880 --> 00:39:55,520
How is that possible?

331
00:39:56,360 --> 00:39:57,520
I'll call IngIng.

332
00:39:57,600 --> 00:40:01,200
The manager already knew.
She resigned without telling us.

333
00:40:02,440 --> 00:40:04,280
- IngIng resigned?
- Yes.

334
00:40:14,400 --> 00:40:17,160
Ith. Ith.
Please don't tell Ms. Lin about this

335
00:40:17,760 --> 00:40:20,000
I know. You've told me a hundred times.

336
00:40:21,440 --> 00:40:22,600
LILIN

337
00:40:23,320 --> 00:40:24,280
Ms. Lin?

338
00:40:27,400 --> 00:40:28,280
What do we do?

339
00:40:31,440 --> 00:40:32,960
Hey, hey, Ing.

340
00:40:34,320 --> 00:40:35,960
MS. LIN, ING'S GIRLFRIEND

341
00:40:37,600 --> 00:40:40,200
- Ms. Lin is calling.
- Don't answer.

342
00:41:17,320 --> 00:41:19,600
Did you order Play Park
to be shut down, Dad?

343
00:41:22,760 --> 00:41:25,960
You shouldn't have interfered
with my responsibilities.

344
00:41:28,600 --> 00:41:32,120
Didn't your manager friend tell you?

345
00:41:35,760 --> 00:41:37,560
So Ing knew about this?

346
00:41:39,720 --> 00:41:42,840
Mr. Pao called and said she resigned.

347
00:41:43,360 --> 00:41:44,720
So she probably did know.

348
00:41:46,120 --> 00:41:49,480
Before you two went to Pattaya, she came

349
00:41:49,560 --> 00:41:52,160
to talk to me for a long time.
You can ask Jane.

350
00:41:53,200 --> 00:41:54,320
Yes, that's true.

351
00:41:55,680 --> 00:41:58,240
I also gave her some money
as a parting gesture.

352
00:41:59,560 --> 00:42:00,400
Did you…?

353
00:42:00,480 --> 00:42:02,480
I didn't throw the money at her.

354
00:42:03,760 --> 00:42:07,080
I saw that she had good intentions
and was willing to sacrifice for you.

355
00:42:08,080 --> 00:42:09,720
I didn't want her to struggle.

356
00:42:11,320 --> 00:42:15,120
She's the head of her family.
She has people to support, doesn't she?

357
00:42:17,880 --> 00:42:20,560
Are you keeping something from me?

358
00:42:20,640 --> 00:42:21,720
No.

359
00:42:23,360 --> 00:42:24,520
Actually…

360
00:42:26,440 --> 00:42:30,600
Ing wanted to save money for Donut

361
00:42:31,120 --> 00:42:33,960
for when he starts school.

362
00:42:40,760 --> 00:42:43,080
Jane, show Lin the transfer slip.

363
00:42:43,160 --> 00:42:44,520
Yes, sir.

364
00:42:46,640 --> 00:42:47,800
Here.

365
00:42:47,880 --> 00:42:50,200
TRANSFER COMPLETE

366
00:42:50,280 --> 00:42:52,400
I was afraid
she wouldn't accept the money,

367
00:42:52,480 --> 00:42:54,360
so I sent it through Mr. Pao.

368
00:42:56,320 --> 00:42:57,520
Lin,

369
00:42:58,440 --> 00:43:01,480
I've helped you through a difficult time.

370
00:43:02,400 --> 00:43:05,120
Now let's move forward
with the tutoring school wholeheartedly,

371
00:43:05,200 --> 00:43:07,240
without worrying about anyone else.

372
00:43:08,160 --> 00:43:10,120
I feel betrayed.

373
00:43:13,880 --> 00:43:16,920
Ms. Lin, things have come to this.

374
00:43:17,000 --> 00:43:19,280
I think you should focus on your work.

375
00:43:19,360 --> 00:43:20,920
You're breaking up with her anyway.

376
00:43:41,520 --> 00:43:43,120
<i>How could you abandon Donut like this?</i>

377
00:43:44,200 --> 00:43:46,000
<i>Do you have any humanity left?</i>

378
00:43:46,080 --> 00:43:48,000
You broke your promise.

379
00:43:49,240 --> 00:43:50,680
You used me.

380
00:43:50,760 --> 00:43:52,080
You're quite clever.

381
00:43:52,160 --> 00:43:54,200
If you were truly sincere with Lin,

382
00:43:54,800 --> 00:43:57,000
<i>you should have helped me</i>
<i>from the beginning.</i>

383
00:43:57,520 --> 00:43:59,680
So you made it easy
for Dad to shut down Play Park.

384
00:44:00,800 --> 00:44:03,360
<i>Can you please reassure me</i>

385
00:44:03,440 --> 00:44:06,040
<i>that I didn't give my heart to a liar?</i>

386
00:46:08,120 --> 00:46:10,920
Subtitle translation by:
Anan Pratchayakul
